0. Edit config.py to suit your setup
1. Insert proxypool.sql into your DB (postgresql)
2. Configure python enviroments anre install requirements (`pip -r requirements.txt`), I tend to name the environment folder `env`
3. Apply the patch `bitcoinrpc-util.py.patch`, this fixes bitcoin-rpc for Python 3
4. Verify that all the scripts work (payout, sharelog, stats). Bitcoin-rpc requires some very small modification to get working in Python 3, just edit the package directly.
5. To ensure the script stay running. I used an upstart script:

    $ cat /etc/init/payout.conf

    start on runlevel [2345]
    stop on runlevel [016]

    setuid doge
    setgid doge

    respawn

    env PYTHON_HOME=/home/doge/sharelogger/env
    exec $PYTHON_HOME/bin/python3 /home/doge/sharelogger/payout.py
